<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-05-10T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-05-10T18:00:00-05:00" n="795" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d795">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/5–649: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-05-10T19:00:00-04:00">May 10, 1949—7
                                p. m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>1517. Urtel 1842, May 6. Too early state at this time what steps US Govt will
                        take re diplomatic reps Canton shld Chi Govt again move capital. Decision
                        will be made at proper moment in light <hi rend="italic">inter alia</hi> of
                        location new capital. Dept keeping in touch with Fr Emb Washington re this
                        and other related matters.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>